UID:570@bwa-calendar
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260601
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260602
SUMMARY:BWA: Parents Morning
DESCRIPTION:Parents are invited to a welcome reception and classroom activities.\n\nParents are invited to a welcome reception from 8:50am to 9:10am, followed by classroom activities from 9:15am to 10:00am. Only one parent per child is permitted. Note: CM2B/Y6B session is postponed to the final French focus week.
CATEGORIES:COMMUNITY
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:633@bwa-calendar
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260623
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260624
SUMMARY:BWA: Heatwave Safety Measures
DESCRIPTION:School remains open during the heatwave. Please ensure children have water bottles, sun hats, and sunscreen.\n\nSchool remains open as normal during the heatwave. Parents are asked to ensure children arrive with at least one, ideally two, named water bottles (frozen recommended), wear a sun hat, have sunscreen applied before school, and wear appropriate lightweight summer uniform. Coats, jumpers, cardigans, and fleeces should not be worn unless there is a specific medical reason.
CATEGORIES:WELLBEING
END:VEVENT
